  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/125650113" />
    <a title="Ummu Auni" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1091055-ummu-auni"><img alt="Ummu Auni" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1439164907p2/1091055.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/125650113?book_show_action=true">Oct 10, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ummu Auni" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ummu Auni" href="/user/show/1091055-ummu-auni">Ummu Auni</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780061968273" href="/book/show/7758019-the-winner-stands-alone">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1091055-ummu-auni?shelf=borrowed">borrowed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1091055-ummu-auni?shelf=read-2010">read-2010</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1091055-ummu-auni?shelf=why-i-read-this">why-i-read-this</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1091055-ummu-auni?shelf=general-fiction">general-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer125650113" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17716241937877581610">For an author who is considered as a phenomenon, Coelho write with narrative sentences, which somehow made the story a bit lagging and too slow unfolding.<br/><br/>The plot revolved around Igor, a millionaire who is bent to get back his ex-wife who&apos;s now married to another man, and he would do anything to get her. And then, there are Hamid, the designer, Jasmine, a model who made it to the top, Gabriella, who wanted to be the one who made it to the big screen, and then, there are other characters as well.</span>
  <span id="freeText17716241937877581610" style="display:none">For an author who is considered as a phenomenon, Coelho write with narrative sentences, which somehow made the story a bit lagging and too slow unfolding.<br /><br />The plot revolved around Igor, a millionaire who is bent to get back his ex-wife who's now married to another man, and he would do anything to get her. And then, there are Hamid, the designer, Jasmine, a model who made it to the top, Gabriella, who wanted to be the one who made it to the big screen, and then, there are other characters as well. Their lives are entwined in such ways, just because Igor wanted to go for a killing spree.<br /><br />As the story unfolds, I couldn't even comprehend the motive Igor had to kill other people, just to catch his wife's attention. There are too many characters, somehow the story weaves in and out through details of many characters, which everyone seemed negative of everything. It seemed too rushed, and I was dumbfounded to find at last that Igor decided it's not even worth it to get his wife back. The motive seemed lost along the way.<br /><br />The title was a little bit struck true. The one who gets it all stands alone. Reading this book, can somehow leave someone in despair.</span>
  <a data-text-id="17716241937877581610" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


